success.question_text:
Jackson found the sixth and seventh numbers in the sequence.

What is the difference between these two numbers?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Algebra, Function and Patterns / Number Patterns

stimulus_1.text: Jackson wrote down the first four numbers in a sequence:

review_3.column_1_text:
The numbers in the sequence are doubling to get the next number.

The differences between the numbers are 2 then 4 then 8.

Continuing this pattern:

  • The difference between the fourth and fifth numbers is 16.
  • The difference between the fifth and sixth numbers is 32.
  • The difference between the sixth and seventh numbers is 64.

The difference is 64.

Tip

success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Algebra, Function and Patterns / Patterns

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

To find a particular term in a sequence, discover the rule and then write out the terms until you arrive at your answer. If the pattern is simple, you may be able to skip terms.

success.question_text: If the pattern continues, what will be the 87th letter?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Algebra, Function and Patterns / Patterns

stimulus_1.text: The letters A, B, C, D and E are used to make a repeating pattern.

review_3.column_1_text:
The pattern has five letters that repeat.

So every fifth letter will be E.

This means the 85th letter will be E.

An A is in the 86th position.

This means B is in the 87th position.

B is the 87th letter.

Tip

A pattern can be formed from symbols and objects as well as numbers. Once the pattern is discovered you can make decisions about the way it continues.

success.question_text: What is the code for the word SMILE?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Algebra, Function and Patterns / Number Plane

stimulus_1.text: This grid can be used to place words into code. For example, the letter G is (4, 3).

review_3.column_1_text:
S is (4, 1), M is ( 1, 2), I is (5, 2), L is (2, 2) and E is (2, 3).

The code for SMILE is (4, 1), (1, 2), (5, 2), (2, 2), (2, 3).

Tip

When naming a point on a grid, the number on the horizontal axis is given first, then the number on the vertical axis.
